This paper focuses on mobile edge computing (MEC) systems, which are typically studied in the computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also involves joint optimization of computation and communication resources, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes algorithms to solve non-convex optimization problems, which is a common topic in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
